  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 height=3D41></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 bgColor=3D#334466 height=3D21><B><FONT=20
      face=3DArial,Helvetica><FONT color=3D#ffffff>SHORT=20
      DESCRIPTION</FONT></FONT></B></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 height=3D104><B><I><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>BFF=20
      </FONT></I></B><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica><B><I>&nbsp;</I></B>is =
a=20
      MAXScript based object exporter under development.</FONT> =
<BR><FONT=20
      face=3DArial,Helvetica>It lets you</FONT> <FONT=20
      face=3DArial,Helvetica>transfer basic object information between =
different=20
      versions of 3ds max using a MAXScript intermediate format.</FONT>=20
      <P><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>No importer is =
required!</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 height=3D41><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>The script =
was=20
      developed mainly to move data from <B>3ds max 5</B> back to <B>3D =
Studio=20
      MAX R3.1</B> in a game development pipeline. Still, it supports =
large data=20
      sets. It has been <B>successfully tested with objects over 800.000 =
faces=20
      </B>and with<B> large number of objects</B> (1000+) and should =
work with=20
      even bigger assets.<BR>&nbsp; </FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 bgColor=3D#334466 height=3D21><B><FONT=20
      face=3DArial,Helvetica><FONT color=3D#ffffff>WHY NOT USE ONE OF =
THE EXISTING=20
      EXPORTERS?</FONT></FONT></B></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 height=3D104>
      <UL>
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica><B>.OBJ </B>does not translate =
all=20
        max-specific properties</FONT>=20
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica><B>.ASE </B>can only export, =
the=20
        unsupported importer is not available for all Max =
versions</FONT>=20
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica><B>.3DS </B>is the main =
transfer data=20
        format in the max world, but&nbsp;</FONT>=20
        <UL>
          <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>3DS does not preserve UV =
coordinates=20
          completely (supports only one TVertex per Mesh Vertex, one =
Texture=20
          Channel) - BFF supports all 100 Channels with multiple =
TVertices per=20
          Vertex.</FONT>=20
          <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>3DS has a data limit of 64K =
faces per=20
          object. BFF supports arbitrary object size.</FONT>=20
          <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>3DS does not preserve max =
procedural=20
          maps. BFF supports the complete max material tree.</FONT>=20
          <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>3DS supports meshes only. BFF =
supports=20
          EditableSplines and procedural primitives, has (limited) =
modifier=20
          stack support and can be extended to support Patches, NURBS=20
          etc.</FONT> </LI></UL></LI></UL></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 bgColor=3D#334466 height=3D21><B><FONT =
face=3DArial,Helvetica>WHAT=20
      IS NEW IN THE LATEST VERSION?</FONT></B></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width=3D628 height=3D104><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>The =
following=20
      improvements have been made to BFF:</FONT>
      <UL>
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>Scene format has been split =
into Scene=20
        and Object .ms files. This lets you quickly disable the loading =
of=20
        single objects by remarking single lines from the main file and =
enables=20
        the import of very <B>large scenes with thousands of objects</B> =
which=20
        used to cause MAXScript memory problems in previous =
versions.<BR>&nbsp;=20
        </FONT>
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>The directory structure has =
been changed=20
        to a more logical hierarchy.<BR>&nbsp; </FONT>
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>Support for Material Editor =
materials=20
        export has been added and enabled by default.<BR>&nbsp; </FONT>
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>ZIP Archive support has been =
added. Now=20
        you can optionally archive all files of an exported scene to a =
single=20
        ZIP file to move to another machine.<BR>&nbsp; </FONT>
        <LI><FONT face=3DArial,Helvetica>Editable Poly support has been =
enabled=20
        through Editable Mesh conversion on import. This means that the =
data=20
        will be exported in the Editable Mesh format and a conversion to =

        Editable Poly class will be attempted when the scene is being =
imported.=20
        If the target platform supports Editable Poly objects (3ds max =
4, 5 and=20
        6 do), the object will end up as EPoly. If it does not support =
such=20
        objects (3ds max 2.5 and 3 do not), the object will end up as =
Editable=20
        Mesh as in older BFF versions.</FONT> </LI></UL>
